<section id="features" class="project-landing-section">
  <div class="project-landing-section-head">
    <div>
      <p class="project-landing-section-kicker">System design</p>
      <h2>The useful parts of your AI work should survive the tab closing.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="project-landing-section-note">
      <p class="project-landing-note-label">Vesti system notes</p>
      <p>Capture, index, retrieve, export. A local memory layer for AI work that normally disappears with the tab.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="project-landing-feature-grid">
    <article class="project-landing-feature-card">
      <p class="project-landing-eyebrow">Capture</p>
      <h3>It records so you don’t have to.</h3>
      <p>Vesti watches for new messages on your chatbot pages. When a conversation finishes, it is saved automatically and silently with no manual steps.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="project-landing-feature-card">
      <p class="project-landing-eyebrow">Timeline</p>
      <h3>Every conversation, one scroll away.</h3>
      <p>A unified feed sorted by time. Platform tags tell you where each conversation happened. Hover to preview, click to read the full thread.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="project-landing-feature-card">
      <p class="project-landing-eyebrow">Search</p>
      <h3>Find anything you’ve ever asked.</h3>
      <p>Full-text search runs across all saved conversations. Filter by platform or date range. Results are instant because everything stays local in your browser.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="project-landing-feature-card">
      <p class="project-landing-eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h3>Your data never leaves your machine.</h3>
      <p>No servers. No accounts. No cloud sync. Vesti stores everything in your browser’s IndexedDB, with export and deletion always under your control.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="architecture" class="project-landing-section project-landing-architecture">
  <div class="project-landing-architecture-shell">
    <div class="project-landing-architecture-copy">
      <p class="project-landing-section-kicker">Privacy architecture</p>
      <h2>A memory layer that stays local, portable, and reversible.</h2>
      <p>Vesti is designed around the idea that AI work should remain searchable without becoming another cloud dependency. The extension writes to browser storage, builds its own local index, and lets you export or delete your archive whenever you want.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-landing-architecture-grid">
      <article class="project-landing-architecture-card">
        <p class="project-landing-eyebrow">Local-first</p>
        <h3>IndexedDB storage inside the browser.</h3>
        <p>Your memory stays on-device by default, close to the tools where it was created.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="project-landing-architecture-card">
        <p class="project-landing-eyebrow">Searchable</p>
        <h3>Structured retrieval without a server round-trip.</h3>
        <p>Threads, prompts, references, and decisions remain filterable long after the tab has closed.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="project-landing-architecture-card">
        <p class="project-landing-eyebrow">Portable</p>
        <h3>Export whenever you need a snapshot.</h3>
        <p>Ship a package, move to another machine, or wipe the archive completely. The memory is yours to keep or discard.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

